Feel that torque?

01:09.539 --> 01:11.605
It's like riding
a hard-on.

01:11.640 --> 01:13.207
Come on, floor it.

01:13.241 --> 01:15.342
My little girl's got
a heavier foot.

01:15.377 --> 01:16.977
I'm going back.

01:17.011 --> 01:18.379
Knock it off, Mikey.

01:18.413 --> 01:20.347
Go on the shoulder.
I want to shoot this sign.

01:20.382 --> 01:22.449
Put the gun away, Jack.

01:23.885 --> 01:25.586
Jesus, what the hell
are you doing?

01:38.131 --> 01:40.166
<i>Arnie, you
should eat something.</i>

01:40.201 --> 01:42.902
How about some leftover veal
and some cold pasta?

01:42.936 --> 01:45.804
<i>Want a beer, honey?</i>

01:56.583 --> 01:58.717
Chicken salad or tuna?

01:58.751 --> 02:00.484
Here come the judge.

02:00.519 --> 02:02.620
What's the difference?
Eat it.

02:05.190 --> 02:07.325
Who says we can't
hire more people?

02:07.359 --> 02:10.695
Why don't you take a nap? Your
face looks like a bag of walnuts.

02:12.163 --> 02:13.797
Everyone should take a rest.

02:13.832 --> 02:15.432
It's an easy thing
to say, isn't it?

02:15.466 --> 02:17.100
You're not thinking.
You're not writing.

02:17.134 --> 02:19.035
Ted, calm down.
You need a nap, too.

02:19.069 --> 02:20.337
Can you believe this crap?

02:20.371 --> 02:21.871
Yes, I can.

02:24.742 --> 02:25.908
Sorry I'm late.

02:25.943 --> 02:27.844
You're sorry you're late?

02:27.878 --> 02:29.879
You couldn't call?

02:29.913 --> 02:31.913
He called.
I told you there's no news.

02:31.948 --> 02:33.349
You did not make that clear.

02:33.383 --> 02:36.285
You really didn't.
You just said "no news."

02:36.319 --> 02:38.220
You didn't say Kenny called in.

02:38.255 --> 02:40.356
- Pow.
- Damn it.

02:40.390 --> 02:42.358
No one cares
that I almost got killed?

02:42.392 --> 02:43.659
What did they say?

02:43.693 --> 02:47.262
It's just like last time, no.

02:47.296 --> 02:49.830
- What does that mean?
- It means they didn't like it.

02:49.865 --> 02:53.668
Then they got drunk, they took
me for a joyride in the Impala.

02:53.702 --> 02:55.903
Why can't we have the Impala?

02:55.937 --> 02:57.472
What did they say?

02:57.506 --> 03:00.341
They said they didn't like 'em.

03:01.744 --> 03:03.610
It's your job to make
them like them.

03:03.645 --> 03:05.579
- Are you not up to the task?
- Don.

03:05.613 --> 03:08.848
What? We've given them seven
ways to go in six weeks.

03:08.883 --> 03:10.550
We don't even get
to talk to them?

03:10.585 --> 03:13.052
We have to depend
on this cripple?

03:13.087 --> 03:14.488
You don't know
what he's up against.

03:14.522 --> 03:16.823
I've got to sit down,
but I'm not gonna

03:16.857 --> 03:18.692
if you're just gonna
continue to insult me.

03:19.693 --> 03:21.494
Just sit down.

03:21.528 --> 03:23.228
They gave me this

03:23.263 --> 03:24.863
and I can't even
show it to you.

03:24.898 --> 03:26.932
What is it?
They typed up their rejection?

03:26.966 --> 03:28.867
It's worse.

03:28.902 --> 03:30.235
They finally gave me
a calendar.

03:30.270 --> 03:32.371
Three years
of monthly deadlines.

03:32.406 --> 03:34.640
That's the rest
of '68, '69, and '70.

03:34.675 --> 03:37.875
Best case scenario, six months
of strategy statements,

03:37.910 --> 03:39.811
every one of them
backed up with copy tests.

03:39.845 --> 03:41.646
<i>And then, if and when</i>
<i>they land on something,</i>

03:41.681 --> 03:43.648
it's got to kick its way up
the ladder through all of GM

03:43.683 --> 03:45.216
until it gets to God.

03:45.250 --> 03:47.118
And then He's got to
run it past His wife.

03:47.152 --> 03:48.687
So what happens now?

03:48.721 --> 03:50.822
You take a swing at it
and they take a swing at me.

03:50.856 --> 03:53.089
They want another packet
Tuesday morning.

03:53.124 --> 03:55.959
- But they want me back on Sunday.
- For what?

03:55.993 --> 03:57.661
I guarantee you
they're not going to church.

03:57.696 --> 03:59.930
We cannot go on like this.

03:59.964 --> 04:01.932
This is what Chevy
is paying us for.

04:01.966 --> 04:03.767
It's not our clock,
it's theirs.

04:03.802 --> 04:05.436
So what's another weekend?

04:05.470 --> 04:07.403
Because they're
really paying us.

04:07.438 --> 04:10.206
Mr. Chaough,
you have a phone call.

04:10.240 --> 04:11.574
Take a message.

04:11.608 --> 04:14.210
It's Nan.
It's about that matter.

04:21.618 --> 04:23.285
Excuse me, Mr. Draper.

04:23.320 --> 04:25.920
Get all the Chevy materials
back in my office.

04:25.955 --> 04:28.590
- We're working the weekend.
- Yes, of course.

04:28.624 --> 04:30.759
But I wanted to tell you
Dr. Rosen is on the phone.

04:32.261 --> 04:34.996
- Do you want me to take a message?
- Yes.

04:35.030 --> 04:38.199
- I'll find out what it's regarding.
- No.

04:38.234 --> 04:40.701
I'll take it.

04:40.736 --> 04:42.936
You know what, Don?
That's a great idea.

04:42.971 --> 04:46.240
I'm gonna call my doctor.
I'm gonna get Kenny here fixed up.

04:46.274 --> 04:48.909
I'm gonna get
everybody fixed up.

04:57.618 --> 04:58.951
Arnold, how are you?

04:58.986 --> 05:00.520
It's me.

05:00.554 --> 05:02.188
Um...

05:03.991 --> 05:05.792
I'm glad to hear that.

05:05.826 --> 05:07.960
Oh, I bet you are,

05:07.995 --> 05:10.397
because I wanted to let you know
that's what that would feel like.

05:10.431 --> 05:12.230
I thought I misunderstood.

05:12.265 --> 05:13.699
Oh, bullshit.

05:13.733 --> 05:16.067
You have got to stop
loitering in my hallway.

05:16.102 --> 05:17.969
Sylvia, I'm glad you called.

05:18.004 --> 05:20.406
He saw all the cigarette
butts out there

05:20.440 --> 05:21.940
and he thinks
I'm smoking again.

05:21.974 --> 05:23.509
I want to see you.

05:23.543 --> 05:25.377
I was in the kitchen
biting my nails

05:25.412 --> 05:27.312
thinking,
"I just cleaned it up."

05:27.346 --> 05:29.280
How many nights
are you out there?

05:29.314 --> 05:31.215
I know you want to see me, too.

05:31.249 --> 05:33.050
All I kept thinking
is he's gonna come in

05:33.084 --> 05:34.886
and ask my why
there's no lipstick on them

05:34.920 --> 05:37.688
and I'm gonna burst into tears
and tell him everything.

05:37.723 --> 05:40.090
Then he's gonna murder me
and murder you.

05:40.125 --> 05:42.760
- Are you afraid of him?
- No.

05:42.795 --> 05:44.594
I'm afraid of you.

05:44.629 --> 05:47.130
I don't think you understand.

05:49.600 --> 05:54.070
Look, I'm too old
to say this was a mistake,

05:54.104 --> 05:56.372
but I want you to try
and be happy.

05:56.407 --> 05:58.341
About what?

05:58.375 --> 06:00.309
<i>That you got away with it.</i>

06:00.343 --> 06:02.711
When you start
something like this,

06:02.746 --> 06:05.047
it takes a lot of convincing.

06:05.081 --> 06:07.850
It's all about whether
or not the other person

06:07.884 --> 06:09.752
has as much to lose as you do,

06:09.786 --> 06:12.688
because you want to be able
to trust them when it's over.

06:12.722 --> 06:16.425
And right now I'm wondering
how I ever trusted you.

06:16.459 --> 06:18.961
<i>I don't really have</i>
<i>a choice, do I,</i>

06:18.995 --> 06:20.795
<i>because you've got me.</i>

06:20.830 --> 06:24.532
So if you ever really cared
about me at all, knock it off.

06:24.567 --> 06:27.202
Don't cry.
Just listen to me.

06:29.138 --> 06:31.940
I'm feeling a lot
of emotions, too.

06:31.974 --> 06:34.475
I'm hanging up.

06:34.509 --> 06:36.710
Please, just listen.

06:38.313 --> 06:41.082
I just want to talk
to you about a few things.

06:41.116 --> 06:43.317
You loved Megan once.

06:43.352 --> 06:46.420
- Stop it.
- Nothing else gets through to you.

06:48.356 --> 06:50.156
I'm going.

06:52.860 --> 06:55.295
Don't make me hang up on you.

06:58.699 --> 07:00.733
I'm hanging up.

07:18.551 --> 07:20.584
<i>Mr. Draper?</i>

07:24.556 --> 07:26.957
<i>Mr. Draper?</i>

07:28.260 --> 07:30.094
<i>I'm gonna go in there.</i>

07:30.129 --> 07:32.796
- Yes?
- <i>Is everything okay?</i>

07:34.199 --> 07:36.333
Yes, I'm fine.

07:36.367 --> 07:38.868
I'm gonna...

07:40.638 --> 07:42.739
I'm tired.
I'm just gonna take a nap.

07:42.773 --> 07:44.908
<i>You do that.</i>

08:04.894 --> 08:06.328
You girls should back away.

08:09.565 --> 08:11.132
Does he have a fever?

08:16.439 --> 08:17.972
You get your bedroll.

08:18.006 --> 08:20.007
You stay in here,
you'll get everybody sick.

08:20.042 --> 08:23.744
- You sleep in the cellar.
- Yes, ma'am.

08:23.779 --> 08:26.213
If the fever doesn't break,
we'll call a doctor.

08:26.247 --> 08:27.981
Better for you
than for everyone.

08:32.220 --> 08:36.623
AimÃ©e, did you leave
that plate in the lounge?

08:36.657 --> 08:39.626
<i>Mr. Draper?</i>

08:41.462 --> 08:44.263
Yes, what is it?

08:44.298 --> 08:46.599
<i>Do you need some water?</i>

08:47.801 --> 08:50.269
No, I'm fine.

08:56.909 --> 08:58.643
Bobby, go get your suitcase.

08:58.677 --> 09:01.580
- That's mine.
- What about Gene's?

09:01.614 --> 09:03.482
I'm not going
to pack his suitcase.

09:03.516 --> 09:04.983
I already did it.
You just have to get it.

09:05.017 --> 09:06.551
Go get it, Geenie.

09:06.586 --> 09:08.987
Go up there and get
Pinocchio and bring it down.

09:09.021 --> 09:11.289
I have to do everything.

09:16.027 --> 09:18.895
- Where's Daddy? We're ready to go.
- I'm taking you.

09:18.930 --> 09:21.565
Were you sitting under the hair
dryer and just remembered that?

09:21.600 --> 09:24.034
Where did you get that skirt?

09:24.068 --> 09:25.469
I bought it.

09:25.504 --> 09:27.238
You mean Megan
bought it for you.

09:27.272 --> 09:29.639
- I earned it.
- On what street corner?

09:29.673 --> 09:31.574
She pays me to babysit.

09:31.609 --> 09:34.076
You're not a hired hand,
you're their sister.

09:34.111 --> 09:36.078
Boys, let's go.

09:43.820 --> 09:45.487
I'm sorry to bother you,

09:45.522 --> 09:47.222
but Mr. Cutler
wants to see you.

09:48.891 --> 09:50.925
It's been two and a half hours.

09:50.960 --> 09:52.093
Do you want to rest some more?

09:52.128 --> 09:53.962
No.

09:53.996 --> 09:56.064
May I clean that up?

09:56.098 --> 09:58.299
Please.

09:59.769 --> 10:02.037
Put the Chevy materials
on the coffee table.

10:04.173 --> 10:06.240
The funeral will be tomorrow.

10:06.275 --> 10:08.609
Frank's family has asked
that in lieu of flowers

10:08.644 --> 10:12.412
a donation be made to the
American Cancer Society.

10:14.382 --> 10:17.151
Frank Gleason
was a great artist

10:17.185 --> 10:18.786
and a great friend.

10:20.155 --> 10:22.556
And he made our company whole.

10:24.325 --> 10:26.325
I'm not gonna be able to work
with you through the weekend.

10:26.359 --> 10:29.729
I apologize, but I'm afraid
this takes precedence.

10:29.763 --> 10:32.498
I'll attend the funeral
if that's all right.

10:32.532 --> 10:34.801
But I can still make myself
available for Chevy.

10:34.835 --> 10:36.368
That's helpful.

10:36.403 --> 10:38.171
I'm sorry for your loss.

10:38.205 --> 10:41.007
He's a piece
that cannot be replaced.

10:49.515 --> 10:51.850
The doctor's here
and I want you to see him.

10:51.884 --> 10:54.986
- I don't know.
- No, he's gonna fix you up.

10:55.021 --> 10:56.922
That's an order.

10:56.956 --> 11:00.091
Can I see him, too?
I did it last time.

11:00.125 --> 11:02.026
We're a team.
If he does it, I do it.

11:02.060 --> 11:03.427
Age before beauty.

11:07.232 --> 11:09.100
How old was he?

11:09.134 --> 11:10.801
Older than you,
younger than me.

11:10.836 --> 11:14.237
You either get used to it
or stop thinking about it.

11:14.271 --> 11:16.039
Sorry about your friend.

11:16.073 --> 11:17.841
Yeah, it's tragic.

11:17.875 --> 11:20.110
I hope we don't lose
Ted for too long.

11:20.144 --> 11:22.311
He doesn't know how
to deal with these things.

11:24.148 --> 11:25.615
Do you feel anything?
'Cause I don't.

11:25.649 --> 11:27.283
He said it takes a minute.

11:27.317 --> 11:29.385
- Well, maybe I need another.
- I'm next.

11:29.419 --> 11:33.388
Actually, Roger, I think
Don should go next. Don.

11:38.061 --> 11:40.028
Pleasure to meet you.
Dr. Hecht.

11:40.063 --> 11:41.997
Don Draper.
Where do you want me?

11:42.031 --> 11:44.833
Anything in your medical history
you want to alert me to?

11:44.868 --> 11:47.802
No, I'm just--

11:47.836 --> 11:49.837
hell, I don't even know
what I'm doing here.

11:49.872 --> 11:51.973
You're exhausted.

11:52.007 --> 11:53.741
I'll need you to turn
around and drop your pants.

11:53.776 --> 11:55.709
- This goes in the gluteus.
- What is it?

11:55.744 --> 11:58.012
It's an energy serum.

11:58.046 --> 12:00.314
<i>Oh? What's in it?</i>

12:00.348 --> 12:02.482
It's proprietary.
But all you need to know

12:02.516 --> 12:05.185
is it's a complex
vitamin superdose.

12:05.219 --> 12:08.789
It's basically my own combination
of B vitamins and a mild stimulant.

12:08.823 --> 12:10.323
You have a heart condition?

12:10.357 --> 12:12.659
No. I thought you said it was mild.
What does it do?

12:12.693 --> 12:15.361
Well, a lot of things.
But I think it'll give you

12:15.396 --> 12:16.830
what Jim Cutler says you need.

12:16.864 --> 12:18.998
24 to 72 hours

12:19.032 --> 12:21.834
of uninterrupted creative
focus, energy, and confidence.

12:21.868 --> 12:24.136
- Really?
- Really.

12:24.171 --> 12:25.771
No one told you about this?

12:28.975 --> 12:30.843
I've visited
some agencies lately.

12:30.877 --> 12:34.445
- You've got a great outfit here.
- Thank you.

12:34.479 --> 12:37.081
All anybody wants to know is what
are you gonna call this place?

12:37.116 --> 12:39.784
Can you tug your drawers
down a little?

12:41.954 --> 12:46.557
"SCDPCGC"?
That's a mouthful.

12:58.602 --> 13:01.504
Stan again.

13:02.974 --> 13:05.108
What do you say, Don?
You think you can beat me?

13:05.143 --> 13:08.644
I want another chance.
You changed course.

13:08.678 --> 13:11.180
- Who's next?
- That'd be me.

13:11.215 --> 13:13.549
- And I have a heart condition.
- Don't worry about it.

13:21.191 --> 13:23.591
Come on, let's go.
Best two out of three.

13:23.625 --> 13:26.361
You can beat me any day.
Let me see the doctor first.

13:26.395 --> 13:27.762
<i>We'll do before and after.</i>

13:46.948 --> 13:49.283
Hey, kid.
Where you going?

13:51.486 --> 13:53.487
Come in here.

14:02.162 --> 14:03.963
Sit down.

14:07.467 --> 14:09.668
Breathe deep.

14:14.874 --> 14:17.175
Is that you?

14:19.112 --> 14:21.146
No.

14:21.180 --> 14:24.149
It's a chest cold. I've
seen plenty of consumption.

14:24.183 --> 14:25.417
You don't have it.

14:25.451 --> 14:27.684
Lay down here.

14:31.656 --> 14:34.491
Your mama don't know
how to take care of nobody.

14:34.526 --> 14:36.360
She ain't my mother.

14:46.538 --> 14:48.705
Can I help you?

14:48.740 --> 14:50.607
Do we know each other?

14:50.642 --> 14:52.676
I'd like to think so.

14:54.646 --> 14:56.513
Can I help you?

14:56.548 --> 15:01.150
I meant from somewhere
other than from this moment.

15:01.184 --> 15:03.820
I don't think so.

15:31.440 --> 15:33.308
- Where's Ed?
- He said his heart stopped.

15:33.343 --> 15:34.476
Roger took him to the hospital.

15:34.510 --> 15:36.277
But they were both laughing.

15:36.311 --> 15:39.247
The strategy is about some
kind of love transaction

15:39.281 --> 15:40.814
between a parent and a child

15:40.849 --> 15:43.317
involving the greatest
gift of all, a Chevy.

15:43.352 --> 15:46.587
I was a child and she was a child
in this kingdom by the sea.

15:46.621 --> 15:48.555
Four score and seven years ago,

15:48.590 --> 15:51.391
this country had some
memorable happenings.

15:52.626 --> 15:55.028
What I don't understand is

15:55.062 --> 15:56.763
is it "Dad, I want this car"

15:56.797 --> 15:59.866
or "Son, I bought
you this car"?

15:59.901 --> 16:03.169
Great, that's two. We need 15
more and we can try another.

16:03.204 --> 16:05.171
In what family is it "Son,
I bought you this car"?

16:05.206 --> 16:08.207
- Good night, all.
- That guy's family.

16:08.241 --> 16:10.609
Did you hear about
Frank Gleason?

16:10.643 --> 16:12.744
Yeah, I guess
dreams do come true.

16:12.779 --> 16:14.679
I think that's in poor taste.

16:14.714 --> 16:17.082
Tell him, Peggy. Tell him
what a son of a bitch he was.

16:17.117 --> 16:18.784
I liked him.

16:18.818 --> 16:20.286
Before he was sick?

16:20.320 --> 16:22.554
I hate how dying makes
saints out of people.

16:22.588 --> 16:25.656
Well, he's obviously
in a better place.

16:25.690 --> 16:28.393
<i>Have a good weekend.</i>

16:28.427 --> 16:30.327
"Dad, I need the car.
I've got a date."

16:30.361 --> 16:33.130
"Dad, everybody at school
has a car but me."

16:33.164 --> 16:35.799
"Dad, I can only go
to college if I have a car."

16:35.833 --> 16:38.101
- "Dad, I--"
- "Dad, I could be dying in Vietnam.

16:38.136 --> 16:39.602
Don't you want me
to have a car?"

16:39.637 --> 16:41.471
Damn it, Ginsberg.
I had another 80 of them.

16:41.505 --> 16:43.840
I got nothing interesting to
say 'cause I'm not on drugs?

16:43.874 --> 16:45.874
No, you just flushed
a toilet in my head.

16:45.909 --> 16:48.877
"Son, I got a car
when I was your age."

16:48.912 --> 16:51.113
"Son, they didn't have
cars when I was your age."

16:51.148 --> 16:54.683
"Son, you can fly till you're
high as an elephant's eye."

16:54.717 --> 16:56.052
That's great.

16:56.086 --> 16:57.886
What are you, class secretary?

16:57.921 --> 17:00.022
I want to write stuff down
so it looks like I'm working.

17:00.057 --> 17:01.990
Fine.

17:02.024 --> 17:04.492
The child is the father
of the man.

17:04.526 --> 17:06.227
Spectacular.

17:19.174 --> 17:21.208
<i>Mr. Draper.</i>

17:21.242 --> 17:23.710
<i>Mr. Cosgrove is here</i>
<i>to see you.</i>

17:25.813 --> 17:27.580
Hello, Kenny.
How you feeling?

17:27.615 --> 17:29.649
My foot's like new.

17:29.684 --> 17:31.718
You think you'll have
new work on Monday?

17:31.752 --> 17:33.686
